Governor Ifeanyi Okowa of Delta State has ordered for immediate enforcement of compliance to assets declaration order, as a precondition for processing of claims due to political office holders and permanent secretaries in the state. The governor’s directive was contained in a statement endorsed by the secretary to state government, Bar Chiedu Ebie, directing all public office holders and permanent secretaries yet to declare their assets, to obtain assets declaration forms from the Code of Conduct Bureau.. It warned that the office of the secretary to the State Government would ensure that all concerned officers tender evidence of assets declaration as a precondition for further processing of their claims.